At least 562 people died in Nepal on Sunday and 196 in India when the deadliest  earthquake since 1950 hit their border region.
Residents ran terrified on Wednesday in  both Bihar state, the worst hit area of India, and in Dharan, the worst hit area of Nepal, as  aftershocks were felt.
No new damage was suffered in either place.
In India's Bihar state  rivers are rising.
Authorities found cracks in the embankments of six of them.
Floods  could be the next threat.
Foreign aid began arriving.
The U.S., Britain and the U.N. are  providing money, medical supplies and teams. 
